{{Orphan|date=February 2010}}{{Unreferenced|date=March 2010}}'''Shophet''' literally, meaning "Judge" was a [[Political]] title of the [[rulers]] of [[Carthage]] and was elected by the people and confirmed by the hundred, to serve as chief [[magistrate]] of the [[Carthaginian Empire]]. The Shophetim did not lead armies, but served instead as the highest political [[authority]] of the city of Carthage.

