{{Orphan|date=May 2011}}The '''Necropolis of Monte Luna''' is an [[archaeological site]] located in the surroundings of [[Senorb?]], in [[Sardinia]], nearby a hill known as "Monte Luna" (in [[italian language|italian]]; literally: "Moon Mountain").<ref name="SC">{{it}} [http://www.sardegnacultura.it/j/v/253?s=18865&v=2&c=2488&c1=2123&t=1 Senorb?]</ref> Excavations at this site have unveiled the remainders of a [[Carthage|Carthaginian]] [[necropolis]], comprising about 120 [[grave]]s. The necropolis was built by the inhabitants of a Carthaginian settlement in the area of modern [[Santu Teru]]<ref>[http://wikimapia.org/2318542/it/Necropoli-Punica-di-Monte-Luna The necropolis at Wikimapia]</ref> around the 6th century BC.<ref name="SC"/>

